The paper deals with the problem of finding dense subgraphs in bipartite networks, which is a common problem in social network analysis, internet advertising, and bioinformatics. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces efficient algorithms for finding dense subgraphs, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions co-occurrence graphs, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed algorithms in detecting spammers, which is a common problem in online social networks (cs.SOC).
